special representative
for international negotiations.

01:28.455 --> 01:32.125 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's now the chief legal officer
for the Trump
Organization.

01:32.159 --> 01:36.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: Shinzo
Abe became
the first Japanese prime
minister to visit

01:36.129 --> 01:38.565 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the USS Arizona Memorial at
Pearl Harbor.

01:38.598 --> 01:45.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
More than 2,300 Americans died
there in the
Japanese attack on December 7,
1941, hurling

01:45.072 --> 01:47.341 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the United States into World War
II.

01:47.374 --> 01:52.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Today, Abe joined President
Obama in a wreath-laying
ceremony before making
statements on the occasion.

01:52.346 --> 01:57.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHINZO ABE, Japanese Prime
Minister (through
translator): I offer my sincere
and everlasting

01:57.918 --> 02:03.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
condolences to the souls of
those who lost
their lives here, as well as to
the spirits

02:03.190 --> 02:08.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of all the brave men and women
whose lives
were taken by a war that
commenced in this

02:08.095 --> 02:13.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
very place, and also to the
souls of the countless
innocent people who became
victims of the

02:13.867 --> 02:15.702 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
war.

02:15.736 --> 02:18.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The Abe visit
came six months
after President Obama visited
Hiroshima, where

02:18.305 --> 02:20.907 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the U.S. dropped the first
atomic bomb.

02:20.941 --> 02:25.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
An outbreak of bird flu in South
Korea is
now that country's worst in a
decade.

02:25.579 --> 02:30.283 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The government said today that
the number
of poultry fowl destroyed will
reach 26 million

02:30.317 --> 02:31.451 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
by tomorrow.

02:31.485 --> 02:34.087 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
That has resulted in egg
shortages and soaring
prices.

02:34.121 --> 02:39.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, a region in China has
culled more
than 55,000 chickens and other
poultry.

02:39.593 --> 02:43.597 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Russian search teams today
recovered the flight
data recorder from the military
plane that

02:43.630 --> 02:45.399 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
crashed into the Black Sea.

02:45.432 --> 02:49.770 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It turned up a mile off Sochi,
where the plane
went down Sunday, killing all 92
people on

02:49.803 --> 02:51.204 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
board.

02:51.238 --> 02:53.740 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Investigators brought the device
to the surface
and sent it to Moscow.

02:53.774 --> 02:58.078 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They say it is not badly
damaged, and could
shed light on what happened to
the plane.

02:58.111 --> 03:01.882 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MAXIM SOKOLOV, Russian
Transportation Minister
(through translator): It's too
early to make

03:01.915 --> 03:02.883 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
any conclusions.

03:02.916 --> 03:04.818 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Various causes are being
considered.

03:04.851 --> 03:09.322 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We will receive a big part of
the information
from the flight recorder that
was found.

03:09.356 --> 03:11.925 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We hope that we will find the
other flight
recorders as well.

03:11.958 --> 03:16.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Russian
intelligence officials
have played down the possibility
of terrorism

03:16.129 --> 03:17.798 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in the crash.

03:17.831 --> 03:22.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're focusing instead on
possible human
error, equipment failure or bad
fuel.

03:22.069 --> 03:27.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Back in this country, melees
erupted at a
number of shopping malls
nationwide last night.

03:27.274 --> 03:31.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Cell phone video captured people
getting into
fights in at least 15 malls from
Colorado

03:31.845 --> 03:33.280 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to Cleveland.

03:33.313 --> 03:36.817 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Spooked shoppers ran for the
exits, and dozens
of people were arrested.

03:36.850 --> 03:41.621 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Police are saying troublemakers
may have used
social media to organize the
fights.

03:41.655 --> 03:45.192 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On Wall Street today, stocks
moved slightly
higher, in a quiet day of
trading.

03:45.225 --> 03:48.562 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 11
points to close at 19945.

03:48.595 --> 03:55.268 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose 24, to a new
record close,
and the S&amp;P 500 added five.

03:55.302 --> 04:00.373 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
