06:43.603 --> 06:45.405 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Lisa Desjardins has our report.

06:45.438 --> 06:50.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: 'Tis the season
for charitable
giving, but charity has been a
long-running

06:50.543 --> 06:56.182 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and controversial topic for
president-elect
Trump, one that he reignited
last night.

06:56.216 --> 07:01.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He posted two tweets, staunchly
defending
the Donald J. Trump foundation,
his private

07:01.221 --> 07:03.823 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
charity, as both generous and
efficient.

07:03.857 --> 07:05.659 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But those tweets ricocheted.

07:05.692 --> 07:08.194 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Some say they are misleading or
plain false.

07:08.228 --> 07:10.130 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So what do we know?

07:10.163 --> 07:11.564 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Let's start with this.

07:11.598 --> 07:15.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Trump tweeted: "I gave
millions of dollars
to DJT Foundation."

07:15.135 --> 07:17.003 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
And he did.

07:17.037 --> 07:22.242 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tax filings confirm Mr. Trump
and his companies
donated $6 million of his own
money to the

07:22.275 --> 07:24.077 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
foundation.

07:24.110 --> 07:25.545 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DONALD TRUMP (R),
President-Elect: I wanted
to make this out of the goodness
of my heart.

07:25.578 --> 07:27.514 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But here's the
issue: Timing.

07:27.547 --> 07:32.585 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tax filings show he donated
nothing to the
foundation in recent years.

07:32.619 --> 07:37.791 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Instead, most of the
foundation's funding,
about $9.5 million, has come
from outside

07:37.824 --> 07:42.362 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
donors, including Vince and
Linda McMahon,
the professional wrestling
tycoons.

07:42.395 --> 07:46.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Linda McMahon is now the Trump
nominee to
head the Small Business
Administration.

07:46.766 --> 07:50.437 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The couple gave $5 million in
two years.

07:50.470 --> 07:55.909 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Next, this claim from Trump:
that all of his
foundation money is given to
charity.

07:55.942 --> 07:58.378 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Again, context is critical here.

07:58.411 --> 08:04.250 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
