08:19.399 --> 08:21.167 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DAVID FAHRENTHOLD, The
Washington Post: They
gave to this group called And
Justice For

08:21.201 --> 08:24.904 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All, which is a political
campaign committee
helping Florida Attorney General
Pam Bondi,

08:24.938 --> 08:29.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
who, at the time, just happened
to be considering,
her office was considering
whether to pursue

08:29.109 --> 08:30.944 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an investigation against Trump
University.

08:30.977 --> 08:34.981 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They, later on, after the money
came in, decided
not to pursue that
investigation.

08:35.014 --> 08:39.018 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Trump paid that money out of the
Trump Foundation,
which is against the law.

08:39.052 --> 08:44.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Finally, Trump
tweeted that
his foundation "never paid fees,
rent, salaries

08:44.057 --> 08:45.925 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
or any expenses."

08:45.959 --> 08:47.694 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That is true.

08:47.727 --> 08:51.364 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
His children serve as the
foundation's board,
and the foundation is run by the
staff of

08:51.398 --> 08:53.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Trump Organization, his
business.

08:53.767 --> 08:58.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now, that creates an efficient
family charity,
