31:32.524 --> 31:36.728 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: Briana goes on to
talk about her
ambitions: to be a gymnastics
teacher, to

31:36.762 --> 31:40.565 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have a husband and children, to
stay away
from drugs.

31:40.599 --> 31:47.639 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BRIANA SOTOMAYOR: "If I grew up
to be like
my biological mom, I wouldn't
get any of these

31:47.672 --> 31:49.508 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
things."

31:49.541 --> 31:56.515 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOTOMAYOR: It was
definitely heart-touching,
and to see a girl, especially 10
years old,

31:56.548 --> 31:58.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to really just be honest.

31:58.383 --> 32:04.256 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: For Briana and her
sister, Riley,
there's a community helping them
move beyond

32:04.289 --> 32:09.961 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
their past, from their new mom
and dad, to
the educators who nurture them.

32:09.995 --> 32:15.300 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I come back and talk to you
when you're
20 years old or 30 years old,
what's going

32:15.333 --> 32:17.969 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to -- what is Briana going to be
like then?

32:18.003 --> 32:21.807 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BRIANA SOTOMAYOR: Well, I'm
going to be old.

32:21.840 --> 32:22.808 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

32:22.841 --> 32:24.676 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
LISA STARK: You will be.

32:24.709 --> 32:35.387 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
BRIANA SOTOMAYOR: But,
hopefully, I won't
be on drugs, and I will be
succeeding in my

32:35.420 --> 32:39.424 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
priorities and just succeeding
in life.

32:39.457 --> 32:44.863 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA STARK: That's a lesson
these schools
are trying to teach all their
students.

32:44.896 --> 32:50.402 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In Jackson County, West
Virginia, I'm Lisa
Stark of Education Week,
reporting for the

32:50.435 --> 32:51.870 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"PBS NewsHour."

32:51.903 --> 33:01.947 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now a look at
some of the
outstanding books of 2016.

33:01.947 --> 33:08.086 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now a look at
some of the
outstanding books of 2016.

33:08.119 --> 33:12.090 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown sat down recently
with bestselling
authors Jacqueline Woodson, the
2016 National

33:12.123 --> 33:17.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Book Award winner for fiction,
and Daniel
Pink, at Politics &amp; Prose, a
popular bookstore

33:17.128 --> 33:18.897 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
here in Washington, D.C.

33:18.930 --> 33:22.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
For Daniel Pink, the highlight
of the year
was Matthew Desmond's "Evicted:
Poverty and

33:22.868 --> 33:24.402 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Profit in the American city."

33:24.436 --> 33:26.471 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DANIEL PINK, Author: This is an
incredible
book.

33:26.504 --> 33:30.108 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's by a guy named Matthew
Desmond, who is
a sociologist at Harvard.

33:30.141 --> 33:32.410 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But this is not a dry, academic
book.

33:32.444 --> 33:36.181 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, it almost reads like a
novel, a very
harrowing novel.

33:36.214 --> 33:40.685 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He spent about a year living in
two different
low-income parts of Milwaukee.

33:40.719 --> 33:44.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this book, I think, shines a
light on
things that middle-class people
don't really

33:44.589 --> 33:46.291 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
understand.

33:46.324 --> 33:48.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First of all, most low-income
people in this
country do not live in public
housing.

33:48.627 --> 33:50.395 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They operate in the private
rental market.

33:50.428 --> 33:54.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The second thing is that they're
spending
60 percent, 70 percent,
sometimes 80 percent

33:55.000 --> 33:57.535 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of their income on housing.

33:57.569 --> 33:59.037 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And it's not sustainable.

33:59.070 --> 34:01.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so what happens, they scrape
together
money for a deposit.

34:01.806 --> 34:03.575 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They pay the first month's rent.

34:03.608 --> 34:05.510 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then they can't sustain it and
they get evicted.

34:05.543 --> 34:10.081 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so these evictions are
happening not in
thousands, but by the millions.

34:10.115 --> 34:11.917 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's actually a virus in the
system.

34:11.950 --> 34:17.956 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so I consider this book in
the same kind
of historical tradition as James
Agee's "Let

34:17.989 --> 34:21.993 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Us Now Praise Famous Men,"
Michael Harrington's
"The Other America."

34:22.027 --> 34:27.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think this book, if you have a
friend who
is a public official, hand him
or her this

34:27.065 --> 34:28.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
book.

34:28.066 --> 34:29.868 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's that important.

34:29.901 --> 34:32.437 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this book raises some
serious questions
about what kind of country do we
want to be.

34:32.470 --> 34:35.140 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: This wasn't on
your list, but
you know this book?

34:35.173 --> 34:36.274 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JACQUELINE WOODSON, Author: Yes.

34:36.308 --> 34:38.376 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm just dittoing everything he
says about
it.

34:38.410 --> 34:39.444 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's such an important book.

34:39.477 --> 34:40.445 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: OK.

34:40.478 --> 34:42.314 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, what do you want to start
with?

34:42.347 --> 34:45.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACQUELINE WOODSON: So, I want
the start with
"Ghost" by Jason Reynolds, which
is considered

34:45.550 --> 34:49.955 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
a -- quote, unquote --
"middle-grade book,"
but it's for anyone who has ever
had a family,

34:49.988 --> 34:53.758 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ever loved running, ever felt
outside of a
place.

34:53.792 --> 34:55.627 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And this book does everything.

34:55.660 --> 34:57.696 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, my 8-year-old loves it.

34:57.729 --> 34:58.964 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
My 14-year-old loves it.

34:58.997 --> 35:00.231 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I love it.

35:00.265 --> 35:02.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it just crosses a lot of
boundaries in
beautiful ways.

35:02.801 --> 35:08.373 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's about a young boy who
joins a track
team.

35:08.406 --> 35:13.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And he comes from an underserved
family, a
single mom and finds a new
family in this

35:13.111 --> 35:17.315 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
track team, but also becomes
this amazing
runner, and has started out by
running away

35:17.349 --> 35:19.484 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from this tragedy that happens
in his family.

35:19.517 --> 35:21.619 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I won't give it away.

35:21.653 --> 35:25.557 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's such a satisfying
story, and you
meet all of these amazing young
people.

35:25.590 --> 35:26.958 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: OK.

35:26.992 --> 35:28.493 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DANIEL PINK: So, I'm going to
give this to
my 14-year-old runner.

35:28.526 --> 35:29.494 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JACQUELINE WOODSON: Oh, cool.

35:29.527 --> 35:30.528 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
DANIEL PINK: But I will read it
first.

35:30.562 --> 35:31.529 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JACQUELINE WOODSON: Yes.

35:31.563 --> 35:32.697 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, Dan,
next?

35:32.731 --> 35:34.065 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DANIEL PINK: Well, I have got
this book right
here.

35:34.099 --> 35:38.203 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
