35:46.745 --> 35:47.679 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: He lived it.

35:47.712 --> 35:48.780 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DANIEL PINK: He lived it.

35:48.813 --> 35:50.815 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And this is about an
extraordinary moment
in time.

35:50.849 --> 35:53.051 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's 1963 to 1965.

35:53.084 --> 35:56.054 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the tumultuousness of that
period is breathtaking.

35:56.087 --> 36:00.892 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's captured, because of
the form, I
think, in this incredibly
cinematic way.

36:00.925 --> 36:05.096 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is a book about violence
perpetrated
against people because of their
skin color.

36:05.130 --> 36:10.135 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
This is a book about
irregularities in our
voting system and the integrity
of our democratic

36:10.168 --> 36:11.669 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
process.

36:11.703 --> 36:14.806 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a book about a world
that seems like
it's spinning out of control.

36:14.839 --> 36:16.474 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
So, it's endlessly relevant.

36:16.508 --> 36:17.776 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JACQUELINE WOODSON: I completely
agree.

36:17.809 --> 36:19.577 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think that's such an important
book.

36:19.611 --> 36:22.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DANIEL PINK: And what is
interesting is that
John Lewis actually got
interested initially

36:22.180 --> 36:24.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the civil rights movement
because of a
comic book.

36:24.382 --> 36:28.520 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So part of it, he's paying
homage to this
tradition that you can tell
serious stories

36:28.553 --> 36:31.122 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and talk about serious issues in
graphic form.

36:31.156 --> 36:33.158 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right,
Jacqueline, number
two?

36:33.191 --> 36:37.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JACQUELINE WOODSON: While we're
talking about
graphics, I have to bring up
Ta-Nehisi Coates'

36:37.162 --> 36:38.129 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
"Black Panther."

36:38.163 --> 36:41.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
